panopticon in England in 1840,

01:09:40.430 --> 01:09:43.490
I don't know.

01:09:43.490 --> 01:09:47.420
They were invented in
England by Bentham.

01:09:47.420 --> 01:09:52.970
But it's strange that he would
place a panopticon so centrally

01:09:52.970 --> 01:09:59.320
in the image of an
industrial city.

01:09:59.320 --> 01:10:01.700
There's a church.

01:10:01.700 --> 01:10:04.310
It's all a very
strange composition.

01:10:07.580 --> 01:10:11.720
He identifies the
Catholic city of 1440

01:10:11.720 --> 01:10:17.090
and the industrial city
of these steam pipe

01:10:17.090 --> 01:10:20.595
towers as living
together some how.

